# Citus Marketing UI Design

You build confident, crafted marketing UI for a dev-tool brand — high-contrast orange accents on dark charcoal, code-native cues, generous whitespace, clear hierarchy. Not generic blue-gray or purple SaaS dashboards.

## Brand Identity (Citus)

**Personality:** Modern dev-tool marketing — precise, code-native, high impact. Confident and technical, not playful or corporate.

**Logo accent:** `#e8551c` — the canonical brand orange. Defined as `--cta-primary` in `app/globals.css`. Maximum impact on dark gray backgrounds.

**Theme:** Dark-first. `<html>` carries the `dark` class by default. Surfaces are deep charcoal (`--background`, `--card`, `--muted`), not flat pure black everywhere. Light mode tokens exist in `:root` but dark is the default experience.

**Accent usage:**
- CTAs, key links, focus rings, hero highlights: brand orange via `--cta-primary`
- Hero gradients: `--cta-primary` → `--cta-secondary` (warm amber-orange family only)
- Tinted section backgrounds: `bg-[var(--cta-lighter)]` or `bg-muted/50`
- One accent family per section — never stack competing colors

**Logo geometry:** Angular, hex-adjacent (60°/120°). Echo through subtle bracket/chevron decorative patterns in heroes — at most one motif per page. Nested panels suggest the logo's layered chevron.

**Code-native cues:**
- Monospace (`font-mono` / JetBrains Mono) for code snippets, CLI output, API labels, and tech badges
- Terminal-style micro-labels sparingly (`$`, `>`, angle brackets) — decorative only, never essential copy
- Sans-serif (Inter) for all marketing prose and headings

## UI Design System & Component Guidelines

### Modern aesthetic

Lean into clean minimalism with dev-tool precision:
- Subtle gradients from CTA tokens — never loud rainbow stacks or purple accents
- **Cards and marketing surfaces:** `rounded-xl` (`rounded-lg` for compact controls)
- **Code-adjacent UI** (badges, code blocks, terminal panels): sharper corners — `rounded-sm` or `rounded-md`
- Micro-shadows: `shadow-sm` on resting cards, `shadow-md` on hover — low opacity, restrained elevation

### Banned styling practices

Do not mix styling approaches. One system only: Tailwind utility classes backed by `app/globals.css` tokens.

- **NO** CSS modules
- **NO** raw inline `style={{}}`
- **NO** arbitrary Tailwind strings (`w-[437px]`, `text-[13px]`) unless a documented token has no utility equivalent

### Interactions (required)

Every interactive element (`<button>`, `<a>`) must have tactile feedback:

```
transition-all duration-200 hover:opacity-80 active:scale-95
```

Match or exceed `CTAButton` patterns for primary marketing actions. Links and secondary buttons still need visible hover and focus states.

## Design Tokens (mandatory)

All colors live in `app/globals.css`. Use token classes only — never invent values in components.

**Brand CTA palette** (source: logo `#e8551c`):
- `--cta-primary` — `#e8551c` logo orange
- `--cta-primary-hover` — `#c94818` darker orange
- `--cta-secondary` — `#f0732a` warm amber for gradients
- `--cta-accent` — `#ff8c42` gradient highlight (warm, never purple)
- `--cta-light`, `--cta-lighter` — tinted surfaces for section rhythm

**Shadcn semantic tokens** (structure and typography):
- Surfaces: `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-muted`
- Text: `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary`
- Borders: `border-border`, `ring-ring`

**Radius:** `--radius` (0.625rem) — `rounded-lg` / `rounded-xl` for marketing cards; sharper radii for code UI.

New tokens belong in `globals.css` only, never as inline hex in `.tsx` files.

## Layout Primitives (mandatory)

Every marketing page follows this structure:

```tsx
<main id="main-content">
  <Section>
    <Container>
      {/* content */}
    </Container>
  </Section>
</main>
```

- **Section** (`@/components/ui/section`) — vertical rhythm: `py-12 lg:py-16`
- **Container** (`@/components/ui/container`) — default `max-w-6xl`, responsive horizontal padding
- **CTAButton** (`@/components/ui/cta-button`) — primary marketing actions (gradient, hover scale, Lucide icons)
- **Shadcn primitives** (`@/components/ui/*`) — Button, Card, Badge, etc. Do not reinvent these.

Alternate section backgrounds with `bg-muted/50` or `bg-[var(--cta-lighter)]` for visual rhythm — not random colors.

## Typography

- **Sans:** Inter via `next/font/google` in `app/layout.tsx` — all marketing prose and headings. Use `display: 'swap'`.
- **Mono:** JetBrains Mono via `next/font/google` — code snippets, CLI blocks, API/feature badges. Apply with `font-mono`.
- **Roles:** one hero display size per page, section headings (`text-2xl`–`text-4xl`), body (`text-base`), supporting text (`text-sm text-muted-foreground`).
- Prefer `font-semibold` + `text-muted-foreground` over excessive size jumps.
- **Spacing scale only:** 4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64 (Tailwind defaults). No arbitrary values like `py-[37px]`.

## Craft and Motion

- **Depth:** micro-shadows on elevated surfaces — not heavy border AND heavy shadow together. Layered panels echo logo nesting.
- **Hero moments:** restrained gradients from CTA tokens (`from-[var(--cta-primary)] to-[var(--cta-secondary)]`). One accent family per section.
- **Motion:** `tw-animate-css` / Tailwind `animate-*` only. Do not use Framer Motion unless it is in `package.json`.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — avoid essential information conveyed only through animation.

## Visual Hierarchy

- Lead with content: headline → supporting copy → CTA → social proof or features.
- Keep related content close; separate unrelated blocks with whitespace, not nested cards.
- Use cards (`@/components/ui/card`) only when content needs a grouped surface.
- Icons: named Lucide imports (`import { ArrowRight } from "lucide-react"`), decorative icons get `aria-hidden="true"`.

## NEVER

- Default Tailwind palette (`bg-blue-500`, `text-gray-800`, `border-slate-200`, etc.)
- Generic purple SaaS accents (`#673AB7`, `bg-violet-500`, etc.) — off-brand
- Light-gray-on-white corporate look as the default page aesthetic
- Hardcoded hex in components (token definitions in `globals.css` only)
- CSS modules, raw `style={{}}`, or mixed styling approaches
- Arbitrary Tailwind values (`w-[437px]`, `text-[13px]`) unless mapped to a documented token
- Nested cards, competing accent colors, decorative UI with no content purpose
- Over-rounded "friendly startup" UI on code-adjacent elements — keep those sharp
- `'use client'` unless interactivity requires it (`useState`, Radix primitives, browser APIs)

## Accessibility

- Semantic landmarks: `<header>`, `<main id="main-content">`, `<section>`, `<footer>`
- Visible `:focus-visible` rings using brand orange (`--ring` in `globals.css`)
- WCAG AA contrast for text and controls
- Touch targets ≥ 44px on mobile CTAs
- Use semantic HTML and labels before adding ARIA

## Class Merging

Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` when combining conditional or override classes.
